T1	Participants 71 97	patients with hypertension
T2	Participants 299 342	patients with mild to moderate hypertension
T3	Participants 494 580	132 subjects in this randomized, controlled trial were in the age range of 40-79 years
T4	Participants 582 905	The inclusion criteria were: systolic BP (SBP) ranging from 140-179 mm Hg and/or diastolic BP (DBP) ranging from 90-99 mm Hg and treatment-naive (untreated for hypertension); or on a regimen of medication for hypertension. Of these 132 subjects, 124 (94%) were already receiving treatment with antihypertensive medications.
